The evidence suggests Sara may have a psychiatric problem. Her symptoms of extreme anxiety, avoidance of activities and locations, trouble sleeping, impatience, difficulty focusing, and infection fear are consistent with Generalized Anxiety Disorder (GAD). GAD causes uncontrolled concern about many things. GAD requires at least three of the following symptoms: Unease or nervousness Fatigue Lack of focus Irritability Strain Sleeplessness Sara's symptoms include irritability, insomnia, and difficulties focusing. GAD also includes her avoidance of activities and locations and infection fears. A competent mental health practitioner should diagnose GAD or other disorders following a comprehensive assessment. Sara's symptoms may have been worsened by the COVID-19 pandemic, which has a major influence on mental health. 